<h3>Users and roles</h3>

<p>
  Start by registerring with your email and whatnot.  Please keep your own
  contact info current (via the
  '<%= link_to 'Edit profile', edit_user_registration_path %>' function)
  because we might occasionally make announcements based
  on your contact information and preferences.  Things like, "work cancelled
  tonight due to trumpocalypse", and the like.  And you'd hate to be the only
  fool waiting for the doors to open up after missing the message.
</p>

<p>
  After you are approved by an admin, you can log in and start accessing info.
  Here's what you can do, based on user role; if you can't do it, don't worry
  about it!
</p>

<div class="row">
  <div class="col-md-4">
    <h4>Standard</h4>
    <p>
      Pick a project, start dialing things.  Mark things as you go.
      You also have quick access to
      all your callbacks and can
      run thru those until they tell you to stop.
    </p>
  </div>
  <div class="col-md-4">
    <h4>Manager</h4>
    <p>
      The exhaulted ranks of... getting to answer the phone.  So when people
      call back in, you can go search and find them.  Plus all the standard
      thingies.
    </p>
  </div>
  <div class="col-md-4">
    <h4>Admin</h4>
    <p>
      Heavy is the head that wears the crown.  The admin is the 'man behind the
      curtain' so to speak, that puts all your leads in here!  Plus all the
      standard and manager stuff.
  </div>
</div>

