<h3>Campaigns &amp; Leads</h3>

<p>
  Campaigns can be created/edited/deleted, and leads can be added, by exhaulted
  <strong>admin</strong> users.  Leads can be added and associated with a
  particular campaign, so that they can always be separated into different
  projects, and different source codes within that project.
</p>

<p>
  But lets say you're just a regular-joe user who wants to call some stuff;
  all you have to do is go to the
  <%= link_to "Campaigns", campaigns_path %> main menu, pick a project, and
  see a breakdown of what there is within that project to call.  Choose one,
  and the next lead is displayed.  Dial it, mark it if applicable,
  and then hit <strong>Next Lead</strong> in the lower-right for the next one.
  When you're done, stop.
</p>

<p>
  Leads are ordered (which one you get for 'next') by how un-recently they
  were dialed by default.  Something that has just been viewed and dialed will
  return to the bottom of the heap.  Certain actions will take the lead out of
  the stack for the foreseeable future:
</p>

<div class="row">
  <div class="col-md-4">
    <h4>Day</h4>
    <p>
      This lead's phone number is daytime-only, and will no longer show up in
      the stack of evening calls.  If someone wants to call during the day,
      they can access these specifically.
    </p>
  </div>
  <div class="col-md-4">
    <h4>Disconnect</h4>
    <p>
      None of this lead's numbers work right.  Either they're disconnected, or
      they are the wrong person when you do reach someone.  A lead found to
      have no  valid phone information will not show up again.
    </p>
  </div>
  <div class="col-md-4">
    <h4>Kill</h4>
    <p>
      Someone who is a valid lead with phone numbers and all that, but has
      asked to be removed.  Also anyone who has left the applicable area or
      died.
    </p>
  </div>
</div>

<hr/>

<h3>Prospects &amp; Callbacks</h3>
<p>
  We also have the ability to 'save' prospects, in the form of 'callbacks'.
  For those times when a sale absolutely, positively <em>cannot</em> be closed
  on the first contact, there is a mechanism for keeping notes and saving your
  own callbacks aside from the general leadbase.  They will stay that way  until
  the user gives them up, or they buy, or say no.
</p>

<h3>User Dashboard</h3>
<p>
  When in doubt, check out your user 'Home'.
   It contains all your callbacks, and a mechanism for setting and tracking your
   own goals.  In addition, there are 'manager' and 'admin' dashboards for all
   the cool extra stuff they can do.  But if you're a regular user, enjoy
   keeping it simple!
</p>

