<h3>Leads</h3>

<p>
  The 'leads' you see in this staging site are generated by the
  <%= link_to "Faker Gem", "https://github.com/stympy/faker" %>, but the app was
   originally developed with uploading real databases of the various venues'
   customer bases.
</p>

<h4>Downloading Leads</h4>

<p>
  The leadbase can be downloaded in <code>.csv</code> format, either at the
  end of the campaign, or at anypoint along the way, to share with the venues
  which leads are disconnected or must be removed from the list.
</p>

<h4>Uploading Leads</h4>

<p>
  The leadbase can be uploaded in <code>.csv</code> format.  The important
  headers which will be used to poplulate the fields are:
</p>

<table class="lead-headers">
  <tr>
    <td>account</td><td>name1</td><td>name2</td><td>address1</td>
    <td>address2</td><td>city</td><td>state</td><td>zip</td>
    <td>phone1</td><td>phone2</td><td>phone3</td><td>source_code</td>
  </tr>
</table>

<p>
  The <code>campaign_id</code> is automatically added based off which
  <%= link_to "campaign page", campaigns_path %> you are uploading leads from.
</p>

